Mauritiusâ€™s stock gauge fell for a
sixth consecutive day to its lowest level in almost 17 months,
led by  State Bank of Mauritius Ltd.  and hotels.  The 38-member SEMDEX index retreated 0.4 percent to
1,791.51, its lowest since Oct. 2010 as of 11:36 a.m. in Port
Louis, the capital.  State Bank , the second-biggest lender by market value,
dropped 1.2 percent, the most since Jan. 31, to 80 rupees.  New
Mauritius Hotels Ltd. (NMH) , the biggest leisure operator, fell 2.1
percent to 70 rupees, its lowest intraday level since March
